**** Package.json is a configuration for npm
**** Webpack Bundler is actullay , parcel, veet basically same
**** two types of dependency
    1. dev dependency : generally required for development phase
    2. normal dependencies: used in production also
**** parcel is dev dependency
**** ~ and ^ diff(tilde and caret)
    ^ is upgrade minor version of package
    ~ is upgrade major versions of pacakge
**** Package.json is a configuration of npm. its keep track of what vresions of pkg installed to our app 
**** package.lock.json : keep track of exact version of that package
**** Every package in node_modules have its own pakage.json which shows dependencies

**** command:  npx parcel index.html
    this command will host App on server
**** npm is installing pkg
**** npx means executing packages

# Remove below line while making production build
  "main": "App.js",

